Brazil â€™s President  Dilma Rousseff 
swore in three new ministers in the capital city of Brasilia.  Rousseff swore in PMDB party congressman Antonio Andrade as
agriculture minister, PDT party general secretary Manoel Dias as
labor minister, and former Strategic Affairs Secretary
Wellington Moreira Franco as the civil aviation minister.  The ministers replace Mendes Ribeiro, Carlos Daudt Brizol
and Wagner Bittencourt, respectively. Bittencourt will take up
the post of vice president of state development bank BNDES.  To contact the reporter on this story:
